# Setting Up Push Notifications with Appwrite Messaging

## Supported Providers

Appwrite Messaging supports the following push notification providers:

| Provider | Platform | Protocol |
|----------|----------|----------|
| **Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM)** | Android, Web | FCM |
| **Apple Push Notification Service (APNs)** | iOS, macOS | APNs |
| **Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM)** | Web | FCM |

---

## Setup Steps

### 1. Configure Provider Credentials

In the **Appwrite Console**, navigate to **Messaging** → **Providers** and add your credentials:

**For FCM (Android/Web):**
- Create a Firebase project
- Generate a private key from Firebase Console → Project Settings → Service Accounts
- Add the JSON credentials to Appwrite

**For APNs (iOS):**
- Create an Apple Developer account
- Generate APNs certificates or tokens
- Upload the `.p8` key or certificates

### 2. Create a Topic/Target

```javascript
// Using Appwrite SDK
const sdk = require('appwrite');

const client = new sdk.Client();
const messaging = new sdk.Messaging(client);

client
  .setEndpoint('https://cloud.appwrite.io/v1')
  .setProject('<PROJECT_ID>');

// Create a topic
const topic = await messaging.createTopic(
  '[TOPIC_ID]',      // Unique ID
  'new-updates'      // Name
);
```

### 3. Subscribe Devices to Topics

```javascript
// Subscribe a user to a topic
await messaging.createSubscriber(
  '[TOPIC_ID]',           // Topic ID
  '[SUBSCRIBER_ID]',      // Unique subscriber ID
  '[USER_ID]'             // User ID to subscribe
);
```

---

## Sending Push Notifications to a Topic

### Using the SDK

```javascript
const message = await messaging.createPush(
  '[MESSAGE_ID]',         // Unique ID
  [                       // Targets (topic)
    {
      target: 'topic',
      topicId: 'new-updates'
    }
  ],
  {
    title: 'New Update Available!',
    body: 'Check out our latest features.',
    icon: 'https://example.com/icon.png',
    sound: 'default'
  },
  {
    subtitle: 'App Update',
    badge: 1,
    tags: ['promo', 'summer-sale'],
    priority: 'high',
    data: {
      key: 'value',
      url: '/home/promo'
    }
  },
  'en'  // Locale
);
```

### Using the REST API

```bash
curl -X POST 'https://cloud.appwrite.io/v1/messaging/pushes' \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -H 'X-Appwrite-Project: [PROJECT_ID]' \
  -d '{
    "targets": [{"target": "topic", "topicId": "new-updates"}],
    "title": "New Update",
    "body": "Check out our latest features!",
    "data": {"url": "/home/update"},
    "locale": "en"
  }'
```

---

## Sending to Multiple Platforms

```javascript
// Send to both Android and iOS users in a topic
await messaging.createPush(
  '[MESSAGE_ID]',
  [
    { target: 'topic', topicId: 'new-updates' }
  ],
  { title: 'Update', body: 'Available now' },
  {
    [messaging.EnumPushProvider.FCM]: {
      clickAction: 'com.app.MainActivity'
    },
    [messaging.EnumPushProvider.APNs]: {
      actionKey: 'View'
    }
  }
);
```

---

## Key Concepts

| Concept | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| **Topics** | Channels for sending messages to groups of subscribers |
| **Subscriptions** | Links between users/devices and topics |
| **Targets** | Define recipients (users, topics, or specific devices) |
| **Providers** | FCM, APNs for handling actual delivery |

## Best Practices

1. **Validate tokens** regularly and remove invalid ones
2. **Use topic grouping** for related notifications
3. **Set appropriate priorities** (`high` for time-sensitive, `normal` for non-urgent)
4. **Include `data` payloads** for deep linking and custom handling

That's it! Your devices will receive push notifications through the configured providers whenever you send a message to the topic.

# Appwrite Messaging: Message Targeting

Appwrite Messaging supports multiple targeting strategies to reach your users through push notifications, emails, and SMS.

## Targeting Methods Overview

| Method | Description | Use Case |
|--------|-------------|----------|
| **Users** | Target by user IDs | Direct notifications to specific users |
| **Topics** | Target subscribers | Broadcast to subscribed users |
| **Targets** | Individual endpoints | Direct delivery to devices/emails/phones |
| **Segments** | User groups by attributes | Targeted campaigns based on user data |

---

## 1. Target Specific Users by User IDs

Send messages directly to users by their Appwrite user IDs:

```javascript
const sdk = require('sdk-name')('PROJECT_ID', 'API_KEY');

const messageId = await sdk.messaging.createPush(
    '[MESSAGE_ID]',
    'New Update Available!',
    'Check out the latest features in version 2.0',
    [],
    {
        users: ['user-id-1', 'user-id-2', 'user-id-3']
    }
);
```

---

## 2. Target via Topics (Pub/Sub Model)

Users subscribe to topics, and you broadcast to all subscribers:

```javascript
// First, subscribe users to a topic
await sdk.messaging.createSubscriber(
    '[TOPIC_ID]',
    '[SUBSCRIBER_ID]',
    'user-id-to-subscribe'
);

// Send message to all topic subscribers
const messageId = await sdk.messaging.createPush(
    '[MESSAGE_ID]',
    'Maintenance Notice',
    'Scheduled maintenance tonight at 10 PM',
    [],
    {
        topics: ['maintenance', 'announcements']
    }
);
```

---

## 3. Target Individual Targets

Send directly to specific endpoints (devices, emails, phone numbers):

```javascript
// Push notification to specific devices
const messageId = await sdk.messaging.createPush(
    '[MESSAGE_ID]',
    'Personal Alert',
    'This is for one specific device',
    [],
    {
        targets: [
            'device-token-abc123',
            'device-token-def456'
        ]
    }
);

// Email to specific addresses
const emailId = await sdk.messaging.createEmail(
    '[EMAIL_ID]',
    'Direct Email Subject',
    '<h1>Hello!</h1><p>Personalized content</p>',
    [],
    {
        targets: ['user@example.com', 'admin@example.com']
    }
);

// SMS to specific phone numbers
const smsId = await sdk.messaging.createSMS(
    '[SMS_ID]',
    'Your verification code is 123456',
    [],
    {
        targets: ['+1234567890', '+0987654321']
    }
);
```

---

## 4. Target User Segments

Define segments based on user attributes and target matching users:

```javascript
const messageId = await sdk.messaging.createPush(
    '[MESSAGE_ID]',
    'Premium Offer',
    'Exclusive deal for our premium users!',
    [],
    {
        segments: ['premium-users', 'active-last-30-days']
    }
);
```

---

## Combined Targeting

You can combine multiple targeting methods in a single message:

```javascript
const messageId = await sdk.messaging.createPush(
    '[MESSAGE_ID]',
    'Campaign Message',
    'Reaching users through multiple channels',
    [],
    {
        users: ['user-id-1'],
        topics: ['newsletter'],
        targets: ['device-token-xyz'],
        segments: ['beta-testers']
    }
);
```

---

## Key Concepts

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    Appwrite Messaging                    │
├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
│                                                          │
│  Users ──────► Direct targeting by user IDs             │
│                                                          │
│  Topics ─────► Pub/Sub model (users subscribe)          │
│                                                          │
│  Targets ────► Direct delivery to endpoints             │
│                  (devices, emails, phones)              │
│                                                          │
│  Segments ───► Dynamic groups based on attributes       │
│                                                          │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

**Best Practices:**
- Use **topics** for ongoing broadcasts to self-selected audiences
- Use **segments** for campaign-style targeting based on user attributes
- Use **targets** for one-off direct deliveries to specific endpoints
- Use **users** for transactional or user-specific notifications

# Appwrite Web SDK: Realtime Subscription for Database & Storage

Here's a comprehensive example showing how to subscribe to both database document changes and file uploads simultaneously:

## Installation

```bash
npm install appwrite
```

## Complete Implementation

```typescript
import { Client, RealtimeResponse, Models } from "appwrite";

// Initialize the client
const client = new Client()
  .setEndpoint("https://cloud.appwrite.io/v1") // Your Appwrite endpoint
  .setProject("YOUR_PROJECT_ID"); // Your project ID

// ============================================
// TYPE DEFINITIONS
// ============================================

type DatabaseEventType = "create" | "update" | "delete";
type StorageEventType = "create" | "update" | "delete";

interface DocumentEvent {
  eventType: DatabaseEventType;
  document: Models.Document;
  timestamp: number;
}

interface FileEvent {
  eventType: StorageEventType;
  file: Models.File;
  bucketId: string;
  timestamp: number;
}

// ============================================
// REALTIME SUBSCRIPTION MANAGER CLASS
// ============================================

class AppwriteRealtimeManager {
  private client: Client;
  private subscriptions: string[] = [];
  private unsubscribeCallbacks: (() => void)[] = [];

  constructor(client: Client) {
    this.client = client;
  }

  /**
   * Subscribe to both database and storage realtime events
   */
  subscribe(
    databaseId: string,
    collectionId: string,
    bucketId: string,
    onDocumentChange: (event: DocumentEvent) => void,
    onFileUpload: (event: FileEvent) => void,
    onError: (error: Error) => void
  ): void {
    // Subscribe to database document changes
    const documentsChannel = `databases.${databaseId}.collections.${collectionId}.documents`;

    const unsubDocuments = this.client.subscribe(
      documentsChannel,
      (response: RealtimeResponse<Models.Document>) => {
        this.handleDocumentEvent(response, onDocumentChange);
      }
    );
    this.unsubscribeCallbacks.push(unsubDocuments);
    this.subscriptions.push(documentsChannel);

    // Subscribe to storage file uploads
    const filesChannel = `buckets.${bucketId}.files`;

    const unsubFiles = this.client.subscribe(
      filesChannel,
      (response: RealtimeResponse<Models.File>) => {
        this.handleFileEvent(response, onFileUpload);
      }
    );
    this.unsubscribeCallbacks.push(unsubFiles);
    this.subscriptions.push(filesChannel);

    // Handle connection errors
    this.client.subscribe(
      ["client"],
      (response) => {
        if (response.events.includes("client.error")) {
          onError(new Error("Realtime connection error"));
        }
      }
    );
  }

  /**
   * Handle database document events
   */
  private handleDocumentEvent(
    response: RealtimeResponse<Models.Document>,
    callback: (event: DocumentEvent) => void
  ): void {
    const { events, payload } = response;

    // Determine event type from event names
    let eventType: DatabaseEventType = "create";
    if (events.some((e) => e.includes(".update"))) {
      eventType = "update";
    } else if (events.some((e) => e.includes(".delete"))) {
      eventType = "delete";
    }

    const event: DocumentEvent = {
      eventType,
      document: payload,
      timestamp: Date.now(),
    };

    console.log(`📄 Document ${eventType}:`, payload.$id);

    // Handle each event type differently
    switch (eventType) {
      case "create":
        this.handleDocumentCreate(event);
        break;
      case "update":
        this.handleDocumentUpdate(event);
        break;
      case "delete":
        this.handleDocumentDelete(event);
        break;
    }

    callback(event);
  }

  /**
   * Handle storage file events
   */
  private handleFileEvent(
    response: RealtimeResponse<Models.File>,
    callback: (event: FileEvent) => void
  ): void {
    const { events, payload } = response;

    // Determine event type from event names
    let eventType: StorageEventType = "create";
    if (events.some((e) => e.includes(".update"))) {
      eventType = "update";
    } else if (events.some((e) => e.includes(".delete"))) {
      eventType = "delete";
    }

    const event: FileEvent = {
      eventType,
      file: payload,
      bucketId: payload.$id, // File ID serves as bucket reference
      timestamp: Date.now(),
    };

    console.log(`📁 File ${eventType}:`, payload.name);

    // Handle each event type differently
    switch (eventType) {
      case "create":
        this.handleFileUpload(event);
        break;
      case "update":
        this.handleFileUpdate(event);
        break;
      case "delete":
        this.handleFileDelete(event);
        break;
    }

    callback(event);
  }

  // ============================================
  // SPECIFIC EVENT HANDLERS
  // ============================================

  private handleDocumentCreate(event: DocumentEvent): void {
    console.log("🆕 New document created!");
    console.log("  Collection:", event.document.$collectionId);
    console.log("  Document ID:", event.document.$id);

    // Custom logic: Update UI, send notifications, etc.
    // Example: this.updateUIWithNewDocument(event.document);
  }

  private handleDocumentUpdate(event: DocumentEvent): void {
    console.log("✏️ Document updated!");
    console.log("  Changes:", this.getChangedFields(event.document));

    // Custom logic: Refresh data, show update notifications, etc.
    // Example: this.refreshDocumentInUI(event.document);
  }

  private handleDocumentDelete(event: DocumentEvent): void {
    console.log("🗑️ Document deleted!");
    console.log("  Document ID:", event.document.$id);

    // Custom logic: Remove from UI, cleanup related data, etc.
    // Example: this.removeDocumentFromUI(event.document.$id);
  }

  private handleFileUpload(event: FileEvent): void {
    console.log("📤 File uploaded!");
    console.log("  File name:", event.file.name);
    console.log("  MIME type:", event.file.mimeType);
    console.log("  Size:", this.formatFileSize(event.file.sizeOriginal));

    // Custom logic: Generate preview, update file list, etc.
    // Example: this.addFileToGallery(event.file);
  }

  private handleFileUpdate(event: FileEvent): void {
    console.log("📝 File metadata updated!");
    console.log("  File name:", event.file.name);

    // Custom logic: Update file preview, refresh metadata, etc.
    // Example: this.updateFilePreview(event.file);
  }

  private handleFileDelete(event: FileEvent): void {
    console.log("❌ File deleted!");
    console.log("  File name:", event.file.name);

    // Custom logic: Remove from UI, cleanup references, etc.
    // Example: this.removeFileFromGallery(event.file.$id);
  }

  // ============================================
  // UTILITY METHODS
  // ============================================

  private getChangedFields(document: Models.Document): string[] {
    // Extract custom fields (excluding system fields)
    const systemFields = ["$id", "$collectionId", "$databaseId", "$createdAt", "$updatedAt", "$permissions"];
    return Object.keys(document).filter((key) => !systemFields.includes(key));
  }

  private formatFileSize(bytes: number): string {
    if (bytes === 0) return "0 Bytes";
    const k = 1024;
    const sizes = ["Bytes", "KB", "MB", "GB"];
    const i = Math.floor(Math.log(bytes) / Math.log(k));
    return parseFloat((bytes / Math.pow(k, i)).toFixed(2)) + " " + sizes[i];
  }

  /**
   * Unsubscribe from all realtime events
   */
  unsubscribe(): void {
    this.unsubscribeCallbacks.forEach((unsub) => unsub());
    this.subscriptions = [];
    this.unsubscribeCallbacks = [];
    console.log("🔌 Unsubscribed from all realtime channels");
  }

  /**
   * Get list of active subscriptions
   */
  getActiveSubscriptions(): string[] {
    return [...this.subscriptions];
  }
}

// ============================================
// USAGE EXAMPLE
// ============================================

// Configuration
const DATABASE_ID = "my-database-id";
const COLLECTION_ID = "my-collection-id";
const BUCKET_ID = "my-bucket-id";

// Create realtime manager
const realtimeManager = new AppwriteRealtimeManager(client);

// Subscribe to events
realtimeManager.subscribe(
  DATABASE_ID,
  COLLECTION_ID,
  BUCKET_ID,

  // Document event handler
  (docEvent: DocumentEvent) => {
    // Example: Update your application's state
    switch (docEvent.eventType) {
      case "create":
        // Add to your documents list
        break;
      case "update":
        // Update existing document in your list
        break;
      case "delete":
        // Remove from your documents list
        break;
    }
  },

  // File event handler
  (fileEvent: FileEvent) => {
    // Example: Update your file manager UI
    switch (fileEvent.eventType) {
      case "create":
        // Add file to your gallery/list
        break;
      case "update":
        // Update file preview
        break;
      case "delete":
        // Remove file from your gallery/list
        break;
    }
  },

  // Error handler
  (error: Error) => {
    console.error("❌ Realtime error:", error.message);
    // Implement reconnection logic if needed
  }
);

// Check active subscriptions
console.log("Active subscriptions:", realtimeManager.getActiveSubscriptions());

// Cleanup when done (e.g., component unmount)
window.addEventListener("beforeunload", () => {
  realtimeManager.unsubscribe();
});
```

